## Context

Thirteenth run. Web search + WebFetch available (PubMed OK; Nature/Springer/ScienceDirect abstract-only). Major focus: fistula spatial atlas (Nature), CMGH myofibroblast fibrotic niche, Acharjee stricture transcriptomics, obefazimod anti-fibrotic ECCO'26, duvakitug Phase 2b maintenance, GALAXI-2/3 Phase 3 Lancet, bile acid-microbiome infliximab axis.

### Journal entries created
- #1101: Nature fistula spatial atlas — McGregor et al. (Oxford). 68 fistulae, Xenium+Visium+scRNA-seq. FAS fibroblasts (TWIST1/RUNX2/OSR2/PRRX1) in concentric zones (LAZ/ALC/FOZ). PMID 41224999.
- #1102: CMGH myofibroblast fibrotic niche — ECM-high myofibroblasts + pericytes as antifibrotic targets. Inflammatory monocytes as upstream stromal activators.
- #1103: Acharjee 8-gene stricture signature — LY96/AKAP11/SRM/GREM1/EHD2/SERPINE1/HDAC1/FGF2. PMID 39977234. GREM1+SERPINE1 overlap with #826/#948.
- #1104: Obefazimod anti-fibrotic ECCO'26 — miR-124 pathway. Pro-C3 ↓50%, α-SMA ↓30% in vitro; collagen ↓45-55% in vivo. Dual anti-inflammatory+anti-fibrotic.
- #1105: Bile acid-microbiome infliximab efficacy — B. catenulatum/TCDCA axis. Microbiome LDA AUC 0.805. FMT mechanistic validation.
- #1106: GALAXI-2/3 Phase 3 Lancet — 1048 patients, guselkumab ~43% treatment diff vs placebo. FDA approved Mar 2025. Still no biopsy substudy.
- #1107: TL1A pipeline update — duvakitug Phase 2b maintenance (55%/41% endoscopic response); ontunisertib STENOVA Phase 2a met endpoints (n=103), Phase 2b H2 2026.
- #1108: Flare prediction literature — no new public longitudinal datasets. SPARC IBD still collecting. Host-microbiome metabolic modeling (Nature Comms) and LIVE framework noted.

