### Key highlights for next run
- Fibrosis pathways now expanded to six: (1) GREM1/fibroblast (#826), (2) TL1A-DR3/Rho (#823), (3) GLIS3/IL-11 (#947), (4) CTHRC1/YAP-TAZ (#948), (5) FAS/TWIST1 (#1101), (6) miR-124/obefazimod (#1104). Drug repurposing should query all six.
- Acharjee 8-gene stricture signature validates GREM1 and SERPINE1 as core fibrosis targets across independent studies
- Duvakitug Phase 2b maintenance confirms durable anti-TL1A efficacy in CD — class validated
- Ontunisertib Phase 2b in fibrostenotic CD on track for H2 2026 — first anti-fibrotic with potential transcriptomic endpoints
- GALAXI-2/3 published but still NO biopsy transcriptomics substudy — monitor DDW 2026
- Still no SPARC IBD / Foli-seq public microbiome release for flare prediction — monitor
- ARES-CD Phase 3 enrolling — monitor for biomarker substudies
- ATLAS-UC Phase 3 results expected Nov 2026
- Anti-TNF data leakage audit (task #805) is highest-priority analysis task — microbiome predictor (#809) is complementary
- Prior tasks still pending — monitor #352-357, #375-379, #408-412, #435-440, #448-453, #743-747, #808-811, and earlier batches
